# Kansas City Chiefs: Team History
[‚Üê Back to Home](README.md)

The Kansas City Chiefs were created in 1960. At first, they were called the Dallas Texans. In 1963, they moved to Kansas City and became the Chiefs.

## Important Years
| Year | What Happened |
|------|---------------|
| 1960 | Team started |
| 1963 | Moved to Kansas City |
| 1970 | Won Super Bowl IV |
| 2017 | Drafted Patrick Mahomes |
| 2020 | Won Super Bowl LIV |
| 2023 | Won Super Bowl LVII |

The Chiefs were one of the best teams in the AFL before the NFL merger. Their early success helped the league grow.

**Famous People From Early Years**
- Lamar Hunt (team founder)
- Hank Stram (head coach)
- Len Dawson (Hall of Fame QB)

The Chiefs play at Arrowhead Stadium, which is known for being crazy loud and having very loyal fans.
